B" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :The schematics indicate the device was manufactured by ''Allwins'' :and the stylized ''P'' is found on other ''Allwins'' products. :''Shenzhen Allwins Technology'' is the presumed manufacturer. ===Reviews=== * [http://www.foxnetwork.ru/index.php/en/component/content/article/36-reviews/92-asus-rt-n10u.html ''Asus RT-N10U B'' Rewieved on '''FoxNetwork'''] :The default clock of the CPU SoC [[Broadcom]] [http://www.broadcom.com/products/Wireless-LAN/802.11-Wireless-LAN-Solutions/BCM5356x-Family BCM5356U] :@333MHz [[MIPS 74K]] in this unit seems to be 300MHz. ===Forum threads=== *[http://wl500g.info/showthread.php?t=28297 '''wl500g.info''' ''thread] about the device'' (RU) - covers overclocking :the [http://wl500g.info/showthread.php?28297-Asus-RT-N10U-N10UB&langid=3&p=242238#post242238 CPU to @500MHz] and upgrading the [http://wl500g.info/showthread.php?28297-Asus-RT-N10U-N10UB&langid=3&p=251117#post251117 RAM to 64MB] :'''RAM''': ''EtronTech'' EM6AA160TSA-5G (32 MB) :>> ''VDATA'' VDD9616A8A-5C (64MB) ===Serial=== ====cpu info====
